        },
        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "Predicting vocabulary of second language learners is essential to support their language learning ; ",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "however , because of the large size of language vocabularies , ",
            "relation": "CONTRAST"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "we cannot collect information on the entire vocabulary . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT-REASON"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "For practical measurements , we need to sample a small portion of words from the entire vocabulary ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "and predict the rest of the words . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "In this study , we propose a novel framework for this sampling method . <S>",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "Current methods rely on simple heuristic techniques ",
            "relation": "CONTRAST"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "involving inflexible manual tuning by educational experts . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "We formalize these heuristic techniques as a graph-based non-interactive active learning method ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "as applied to a special graph . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "We show ",
            "relation": "EVALUATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "that by extending the graph , ",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "we can support additional functionality ",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "such as incorporating domain specificity ",
            "relation": "EXEMPLIFICATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 14,
            "text": "and sampling from multiple corpora . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "In our experiments , we show ",
            "relation": "EVALUATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 17,
            "parent": 16,
            "text": "that our extended methods outperform other methods in terms of vocabulary prediction accuracy ",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 18,
            "parent": 17,
            "text": "when the number of samples is small . <S>",
            "relation": "CONDITION"
        }
    ]
}